===Verb===
{{en-verb|*}}

# {{lb|en|ambitransitive}} To stop [[trading]] as a [[business]].
#: {{ux|en|The local factory will '''close down''' soon, unless sales pick up.}}
#: {{ux|en|They had to '''close''' the mine '''down''' as it was in a dangerous condition.}}
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2022 December 14|author=Christian Wolmar|title=Productivity should play no part in pay negotiations|journal=RAIL|issue=972|page=46|text=Eventually the NUR overplayed its hands with an all-out strike. And when Peter Parker, the then-chairman of BR, who was well regarded among his staff, called their bluff by threatening to '''close down''' the entire network, they caved in.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[surround]] someone, as to [[impede]] their movement.
#: ''If anyone passes to Smith, '''close him down'''.''

